column5: Stop rubbing it in. You're making me loose concentration & not get any work done.
Yuuuuuummmmmmmyyyyy.  Looks great G.  Nice mess of fish you got there.  Joey
cruel report  I spent all day xmas shopping. Very nice crappie
Well if you are gonna invite me to a fish fry you gotta tell me BEFORE you eat them...GEEEEEZ   Nice catch there Glen !!!
congrats on the catch and it looks tasty
Not only did you NOT pick me up on the way, you ate all the fish!  Nice job there Glen.....the scenery shots were a nice addition!

Very nice catch of fish glen !!!!!   looks like a great area with lots of structure from those points.....well those fish look great buddy...too bad i missed dinner,LOL..LOL..LOL. great pics too,you had a very productive day my friend !!!...cheers
Not so bad there bud.Rumor has it that Art caught a mess of sac-o-lait today for dinner tomorrow night.Dunno if he got pics before he field dressed them! Joe
Hey, that's a tasty looking haul Glenn.  Sweet !!!

Hey Glen...great description and pics of your fishing spot....could ya post the GPS coordinates next time???  Great day of fishing....nice temps....and a great meal at the end of the day.  I'll PM you my address...next time you have a fish fry, please mail me some.
nice pics!...certainly looks good enough to eat!.. but what is that god awful green stuff? it does not look like it is in the meat group to me!  G

Mmmmmmmmmm...now THAT'S a report!  Love the pics especially the ones at the dinner table!  I enjoy my fish whole like that too.  Looks great on the plate and, you're right, you waste way less of it.  I kinda think it tastes better too!  Thanks for that!
Ok Glen,now I'm really hungry and its only 7.23 am... Great report bud...Wish I could of been there to help you out with that mess of fish... Now excuse me while I go fix up a bowl of cereal.....
....I wake up to approx. ten inches of snow and your posting open water reports followed by a scrumptious looking meal! Why I oughta .........
Beauty report, nice haul, good feed... now I'm hungry...
You're a cruel man ... Glen .... a cruel man. I can only imagine how a hot mess of fress fish would taste right about now.
'Nuther great report Bubba but still no dam fish eh? I especially enjoyed the play by play on how to eat a crappie. Did Missey get to eat any fish at all ?
what an awesome mixed bag!!! thanks for the eye candy Glen!  bring on spring!!! haha  cheers, UF

Sorry folks but my camera is in the shop getting repaired so no pictures but I did get a 16keepers of Soc olait big fish was 14 inches and smallest kept was 12. I got the potato wedges sitting in a bucket of cold saltwater getting ready for the fish fry tonight.   Art
Them was some kinda good vittles to be sure.Sac-a-lait,potatoes and green beans.Whats not to like? Joe
that report made me real hungry!
Nice fish,s dawg. Nice look,n eats too. What the heck is that green stuff. LOL  Thanks for sharing.
Fantastic report Glen - and thanks for the tip on cooking the smaller crappie, gotta try it someday.
